<br>
This would be for the lvl 60's with AA but hey give us all something to shoot for.<br>
<br>
1.) Why should paladins and sk's get horses only?  Wouldn't it make sense for a warrior to have a horse as an AA skill also?<br>
<br>
2.) The whole Assasinate Skill rogues get, warriors should have something akin to that, as in the decapitation idea, or use whatever semantics you want but that would be only fair too.<br>
<br>
Just some thoughts.  We shouldnt get spells, or uber skills, but clerics are far ahead of other healers, warriors should be ahead of others tanks in both ac and hp's.<br>
<br>
Maybe give warriors a higher hp bonus for stamina.<br>
<br>
Much of the posts here are not class envy, but simply some common sense additions that are being left out.<br>
<br>
One question to end....how many today would still start from square one and roll up a warrior as a melee, or presently would you choose something else?<br>
